notesStmt.note: Much stained or blurred in parts, occasionally also a little damaged. Imperfect at the beginning and also having lacunae between some leaves in the body of the mss.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: The book of Exodus with a verse-by-verse translation into Aramaic, an Arabic translation of Sa'adia Gaon, and provided with the simple superlinear punctuation.
msContents.textLang: Hebrew; Jewish Babylonian Aramaic (ca. 200-1200 CE); Judeo-Arabic

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 24; written lines: 24; The writing depends from the ruled line. Visible pricking. Ruling with hard-point is visible, lines ruled on the flesh side. Manuscript imperfect at the beginning and at the end.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite square script with punctutation, probably of 15th century.

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 23 July 1881.
